comments.raw_text:
The relevant styles are:

  a,a:visited,a:link,a:active {
    border-bottom: 1px solid #fbb917;
  }

  a.menu:hover {
    border-bottom: none;
    background-color: #fbb917;
  }

So if you hover over the bottom border, the :a goes into hover state and that will make the border go away, which takes it out of hover state, etc.

The only question is why the synthetic mousemove recursion protection doesn't handle this.

